                <div class="modal-body p-5">
                    <h5 class="mb-4">Latest Works</h5>
                    <div class="container-fluid">
                        <p style="text-align: justify;color: #000;font-size: 18px;">Wim Jay Fernando is a stylist who provides services and advice to famous celebrities and organizations to help them look and feel their best. He has worked on in a variety of setting such as but not limited to photo shoots, TV Shows, Sitcom, film sets, fashion show, commercials, and personal styling consultations. <br><br>Wim grew up in the province of Nueva Vizcaya and eldest child of his parents. He always had love and interest in fashion and beauty, in fact when he was high school student, he loved playing paper dolls, sketching clothes and designing costumes. Despite his desire to become stylist, Wim had to finish non-fashion studies in order to help and provide the needs of his family as their eldest child.  He earned a bachelor’s degree in Hotel and Restaurant Management. But destiny had better plans for him, despite not being able to obtain a degree in fashion, he was able to obtain a job in this field. <br><br>After graduation, Wim landed a job as an Art Dept. boy under the department of Production Designer. During his time there, he eventually learned the process of the industry and further developed his skills. After being an Art dept. boy, he became an associate stylist and make-up artist. His love, passion, dedication, and unique abilities pushed him to continue his career and enter the world of styling.<br><br>Wim worked his way up over the years and eventually became a lead stylist himself. He worked and continues to work on wardrobe styling for events, commercials, television shows, movies, soap operas, and variety shows, etc. His first client to style personally was Ms. Jodi Santa Maria. Now, he worked with over 50 famous and veteran celebrities including, Ms. Gina Alajar, Ms. Maja Salvador, Angeline Quinto, Toni and Alex Gonzaga, Joey De Leon, Piolo Pascual, Sunshine Cruz, Bela Padilla, Jasmine Curtis, Kakai Bautista, Miles Ocampo,Yayo Aguila, Gardo Versoza,  Aljur Abrenica, Ruru Madrid, Katrina Halili,  Wendel Ramos,  Jillian Ward, Sofia Pablo and many more. <br><br>As a stylist, there are challenges that he also encountered throughout his career, he considered searching and pre-production of the garments was the most challenging part. But he make sure to remain calm and optimistic and able to manage his time effectively to settle and overcome this challenges. Wim believes that everyone deserves to feel confident and comfortable, which he always makes an effort to talk and listen to his client regarding their preference while ensuring that the final output is trendy, fashionable, and applicable with the look and figure of the client using his signature style. <br><br>Today, Wim Jay is one of the most sought-after stylists in the industry, known for his impeccable taste and attention to detail. He is constantly pushing boundaries boundaries of fashion and beauty, always seeking out innovative ways to help his client look and feel their best. <br><br>Wim’s advice to anyone interested pursuing a career in styling, “Love and embrace what you are doing and always put your heart into everything that you do, because success requires persistence”</p>
